nformation Management  What to Expect      What to Expect     UIC’s health information management curriculum integrates coursework with professional practice experience in affiliated healthcare facilities. Several of our classes are offered online.  The length of our program is two years full-time, three years part-time. Both require 63 credits for graduation. Below is a sample full-time schedule.          Year 1    Year 1    Year 2         Pre-BHIS    Fall    Spring       AHS Summer Exploration and Transition      Looking for an exciting, well-connected jump start to college? Let us help with AHS:SET!  Applied Health Sciences: Summer Exploration and Transition Institute (AHS:SET) meets 2 days in the summer to engage and prepare our AHS incoming freshmen and transfer students.  In a fun and interactive format, you’ll get exposed to introductory academic course work, research and tools for navigating the rigors of an applied health sciences degree.  Sharpen your skills, make connections and learn about the College of Applied Health Sciences (AHS), all before your first semester at UIC!      Find out more and register        Required courses        HIM 317  Principles of Health Information Management  4 hours    HIM 410  Introduction to the Health Care System  3 hours    BHIS 405  Medical Sciences and Human Pathophysiology  3 hours    BHIS 406  Medical Terminology for Health Information Management  2 hours    BHIS 460  Introduction to Health Informatics  1 hour    BHIS 461  Information Systems for Health Information Management  2 hours    BHIS 480  Management and Business Practices  3 hours          Required courses        HIM 319  Alternative Health Records  4 hours    HIM 320  Technical Affiliation  2 hours    HIM 329  Legal Aspects of Health Information Management  3 hours    HIM 337  Analysis of Health Care Data  4 hours    HIM 432  Coding and Classification Systems  3 hours             Fall    Spring       Required courses        BHIS 410  Health Data Structures and Management  3 hours    HIM 343  Quality Evaluation and Management  3 hours    HIM 361  Human Resources Management  4 hours    HIM 433  Coding and Reimbursement Systems  4 hours    HIM 481  Healthcare Financial Management  2 hours          Required courses        HIM 367  System Analysis and Design  3 hours    HIM 374  Health Information Research  3 hours    HIM 377  Current Issues in HIM  2 hours    HIM 384  Clinical Practicum  5 hours              Biomedical and Health Information Sciences    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          BS in Health Information Management    Expand BS in Health Information Management menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    Expand Applying menu          Transferring from another UIC program      After You Apply      Minor in Life Science Visualization    Expand Minor in Life Science Visualization menu          What to Expect    Applying      MS in Biomedical Visualization    Expand MS in Biomedical Visualization menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Meet Our Students    Expand Meet Our Students menu          Class of 2020    Class of 2021        MS in Health Informatics    PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics    Expand PhD in Biomedical and Health Informatics menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty      Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Information Management    Post-Master’s Certificate in Health Informatics    Post-Baccalaureate Certificate in Health Informatics      News    Calendar    Directory    Contact                College of  Applied Health  Sciences       UI Health Logo                            Quick Links    Calendar    Directory    News    Inside AHS    Graduation      Resources    Academic Support and Achievement Program    Student Resources    Faculty and Staff Resources    Academic Calendar      Tools    myUIC    GoogleApps@U